title: Annual State of NASA Address, Media Budget Briefing Set for March 28
summary: NASA Administrator Bill Nelson will give the 2022 State of NASA address at 2 p.m. EDT on Monday, March 28, from NASA’s Kennedy Space Center in Florida.

title: Hydrazine fueling operations underway for SLS booster steering system
summary: Technicians wearing protective self-contained suits are loading toxic hydrazine fuel into the Space Launch System’s hydraulic power units Friday on pad 39B at the Kennedy Space Center. NASA is gearing up for a countdown dress rehearsal which could start as soon as Apr. 1.

title: SpaceX’s new Dragon spaceship named ‘Freedom’
summary: SpaceX’s fourth human-rated Crew Dragon spacecraft has been named “Freedom” by the first team of astronauts who will ride it into orbit next month.

title: NASA gives priority to Artemis ground test over commercial astronaut launch
summary: NASA officials gave the green light Friday for the first all-commercial astronaut launch to the International Space Station on a SpaceX rocket as soon as April 3. But the astronaut launch could be delayed a day, or longer, to give priority to a countdown test for NASA’s Space Launch System moon rocket on a neighboring launch pad at the Kennedy Space Center.
